SG.DMK.ALLD.FN.ZS-publicLifeDecisionMaki.def: Women participating in the three decisions (own health care, major household purchases, and visiting family) is the percentage of currently married women aged 15-49 who say that they alone or jointly have the final say in all of the three decisions (own health care, large purchases and visits to family, relatives, and friends).
SG.DMK.ALLD.FN.ZS-publicLifeDecisionMaki.name: Women participating in the three decisions
SG.DMK.ALLD.FN.ZS-publicLifeDecisionMaki.units: own health care, major household purchases, and visiting family) (% of women age 15-49

SG.DMK.SRCR.FN.ZS-publicLifeDecisionMaki.def: Proportion of women ages 15-49 years (married or in union) who make their own decision on all three selected areas i.e. can say no to sexual intercourse with their husband or partner if they do not want; decide on use of contraception; and decide on their own health care. Only women who provide a “yes” answer to all three components are considered as women who “make her own decisions regarding sexual and reproductive”.
SG.DMK.SRCR.FN.ZS-publicLifeDecisionMaki.name: Women making their own informed decisions regarding sexual relations, contraceptive use and reproductive health care
SG.DMK.SRCR.FN.ZS-publicLifeDecisionMaki.source: Demographic and Health Surveys compiled by United Nations Population Fund
SG.DMK.SRCR.FN.ZS-publicLifeDecisionMaki.dataset: Demographic and Health Surveys compiled by United Nations Population Fund

SG.GEN.PARL.ZS-publicLifeDecisionMaking.def: Women in parliaments are the percentage of parliamentary seats in a single or lower chamber held by women.
SG.GEN.PARL.ZS-publicLifeDecisionMaking.name: Proportion of seats held by women in national parliaments
SG.GEN.PARL.ZS-publicLifeDecisionMaking.source: Inter-Parliamentary Union (IPU) (www.ipu.org).  For the year of 1998, the data is as of August 10, 1998.
SG.GEN.PARL.ZS-publicLifeDecisionMaking.dataset: Inter-Parliamentary Union (IPU) (www.ipu.org).  For the year of 1998, the data is as of August 10, 1998.

SG.LAW.INDX-publicLifeDecisionMaking.def: The index measures how laws and regulations affect women’s economic opportunity.  Overall scores are calculated by taking the average score of each of the eight areas (Going Places, Starting a Job, Getting Paid, Getting Married, Having Children, Running a Business, Managing Assets and Getting a Pension), with 100 representing the highest possible score.
SG.LAW.INDX-publicLifeDecisionMaking.name: Women Business and the Law Index Score
SG.LAW.INDX-publicLifeDecisionMaking.source: World Bank: Women, Business and the Law. https://wbl.worldbank.org/
SG.LAW.INDX-publicLifeDecisionMaking.dataset: World Bank: Women, Business and the Law. https://wbl.worldbank.org/
